  "prompt": "How do you take a screenshot on a Mac?",
  "response": "On a Mac, there are several ways to take a screenshot:\n\n1. Full Screen Screenshot:\n\u2022 Press Command (\u2318) + Shift + 3\n\u2022 The entire screen will be saved to your desktop\n\n2. Partial Screen Screenshot:\n\u2022 Press Command (\u2318) + Shift + 4\n\u2022 Your cursor turns into a crosshair\n\u2022 Click and drag to select the area you want to capture\n\u2022 Release the mouse button to take the screenshot\n\n3. Specific Window Screenshot:\n\u2022 Press Command (\u2318) + Shift + 4\n\u2022 Then press Spacebar\n\u2022 Your cursor turns into a camera icon\n\u2022 Click on the window you want to capture\n\n4. Touch Bar Screenshot (if applicable):\n\u2022 Press Command (\u2318) + Shift + 6\n\n5. Using Screenshot App:\n\u2022 Press Command (\u2318) + Shift + 5\n\u2022 This opens a screenshot toolbar with more options like screen recording\n\nAll screenshots are typically saved to the desktop by default, unless you specify a different location in the Screenshot app settings.",
